{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Storing a PASS review summary is blocked when any stored dimension finding for the same round has a FAIL verdict.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is between summary-persistence logic and stored per-dimension findings for the same round. A unit test of a pure aggregator can miss round-scoping/query wiring bugs; this behavior is specifically about persisted state cross-checking before write.","test_description":"Seed local storage with findings for round R including at least one FAIL. Attempt to save a PASS summary for round R through the real review-summary service path. Assert the write is rejected (or transaction rolled back) and an explicit validation error is returned.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.24,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Stop-gate verdict computation reads per-dimension stored findings directly and does not rely only on hand-written summary text.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is a module-handoff/data-source-of-truth behavior: gate computation must query stored findings and ignore contradictory summary text. A unit test on verdict logic alone may not catch incorrect data-source wiring.","test_description":"Persist findings for round R with one FAIL, and also persist/edit summary text that claims all PASS. Run stop-gate verdict computation via the real gate service/repository wiring. Assert verdict is non-PASS and that the decision trace references stored findings, not summary prose.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Manual summary text overrides require an explicit override flag and produce an auditable warning record.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The behavior spans request validation plus durable audit side effects. A unit test can validate flag checks but can miss missing/incorrect audit-record wiring, which is central to the failure mode.","test_description":"Invoke summary update without override flag while changing generated summary text; assert rejection. Invoke with explicit override flag; assert success and that a warning/audit record is persisted with actor, timestamp, and reason metadata.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"After Phase 4 fixes, the review loop cannot finalize PASS unless a fresh review-agent round is executed on the updated diff.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is lifecycle/state coordination across diff versioning, round tracking, and finalization gate. Correctness does not require real LLM output; it requires correct wiring of freshness checks across modules.","test_description":"Create a round on diff D1 with prior results, then apply fixes producing D2. Attempt to finalize PASS without running a new review round on D2; assert blocked. Run a new round tied to D2, then re-attempt finalization; assert only then it may proceed.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.14,"Integration":0.71,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"If review rounds are exhausted with unresolved MUST-FIX findings, the flow emits an escalation outcome instead of PASS.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure appears in orchestration over persisted findings + round budget policy. It is not primarily LLM-quality-dependent; the key is policy application across modules/state transitions.","test_description":"Configure max rounds N, seed/find unresolved MUST-FIX findings through the final allowed round, and run the flow controller to completion. Assert terminal outcome is ESCALATION (or equivalent) and PASS is impossible while MUST-FIX remains unresolved.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.17,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
